FBIS4-28660 "dreas113_a_94017" FBIS-EAS-94-113 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Telecommunications Talks With PRC Set for 15 Jun Telecommunications Talks With PRC Set for 15 Jun OW1306104394 Tokyo KYODO in English 0927 GMT 13 Jun 94 OW1306104394 Tokyo KYODO English BFN [Text] Tokyo, June 13 KYODO -- Japan and China will hold talks Wednesday [15 June] on the telecommunications and postal service fields, officials at Japan's Posts and Telecommunications Ministry said Monday. They said representatives from both countries' posts and telecommunications ministries will discuss schedules for setting up a proposed forum for bilateral cooperation. The forum is expected to become a stage whereby government and private-sector representatives from both countries can exchange opinions and information. Representatives will also discuss plans by Japanese firms to help upgrade the information infrastructure in Nanjing and Shanghai through research and development projects, the officials added.
